Busia County Commissioner Joseph Kanyiri said the complaints were being investigated.
The administrator said land issues are matters of life and death and proper procedures and due process, which involve spousal consent and the transactions going through land boards, should be adhered to.
“Some basic requirements must be adhered to for any transaction to be legitimate. Anything less is null and void,” said Mr Kanyiri. Ogiek community challenges the decision to issue title deeds. Owners will be able to use title deeds as collateral in acquiring bank loans. Sonko defends himself on second day of impeachment sitting. Sonko accuses mover of the impeachment motion of dramatising the bursary issue to protect a powerful cartel of MCAs. Somalia’s President facing accusations of misusing foreign-trained police units to harass top presidential contenders.